org.apache.poi.hwpf.model

Class ListLevel

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.poi.hwpf.model.ListLevel

  • @Internal
public final class ListLevel
extends java.lang.Object
    "The LVL structure contains formatting information about a specific level in a list. When a paragraph is formatted as part of this level, each placeholder in xst is replaced with the inherited level number of the most recent or current paragraph in the same list that is in the zero-based level specified by that placeholder. The level number that replaces a placeholder is formatted according to the lvlf.nfc of the LVL structure that corresponds to the level that the placeholder specifies, unless the lvlf.fLegal of this LVL structure is nonzero." -- Page 388 of 621 -- [MS-DOC] -- v20110315 Word (.doc) Binary File Format(“LVL结构包含有关列表中特定级别的格式信息。当段落被格式化为此级别的一部分时，xst中的每个占位符都会被替换为同一列表中最近或当前段落的继承级别号，该列表位于该占位符指定的从零开始的级别中。替换占位符的级别号根据与占位符指定的级别相对应的LVL结构的lvlf.nFC进行格式化，除非此LVL结构的lvlf.fLegal是非零。“--第388页，共621页-- [MS-Doc] -- v20110315 Word（.Doc）二进制文件格式)

      • getRestart

        public short getRestart()
        An unsigned integer that specifies the first (most-significant) zero-based level after which the number sequence of this level does not restart. The number sequence of this level does restart after any level that is more significant than the specified level. This MUST be less than or equal to the zero-based level of the list to which this LVLF corresponds.

        see [MS-DOC], v20140721, 2.9.150

        (一个无符号整数，指定第一个（最高有效）从零开始的级别，此后此级别的数字序列不会重新启动。此级别的数字序列确实会在任何比指定级别更重要的级别之后重新启动。这必须小于或等于此LVLF对应的列表的从零开始的级别。请参阅[MS-Doc]，v20140721，2.9.150)
        Returns:
        the first (0 is the most significant) level after which the numbering does not restart or -1 if no restart is applicable(第一个（0是最重要的）级别之后编号不会重新启动，或者如果不重新启动，则为-1)

      • isLegalNumbering

        public boolean isLegalNumbering()
        Determines if the number formatting shall be overridden by msonfcArabic; unless it originally was msonfcArabicLZ in which case it is preserved.

        see [MS-DOC], v20140721, 2.9.150 and [MS-OSHARED], v20140721, 2.2.1.3

        (确定数字格式是否应由msonfcArabic覆盖;除非它最初是msonfcArabicLZ，在这种情况下将保留。请参阅[MS-Doc]，v20140721，2.9.150和[MS-OSHARED]，v20140721，2.2.1.3)
        Returns:
        true if the level numbering of this and all more significant levels must be overridden; false otherwise(如果必须重写此级别和所有更重要级别的级别编号，则为真;否则为假)
